<item>
            <title>[HBASE-4130] HTable.flushCommits throws IndexOutOfBoundsException</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-4130</link>
                <project id="12310753" key="HBASE">HBase</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Using a HTable instance with auto commit disabled in multiple thread may raise IndexOutOfBoundsException , as the processBatchOfPuts remove the commited results by their index which may be wrong as the list size shortened by other thread.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;the following is the stack trace.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;java.lang.IndexOutOfBoundsException: Index: 3781, Size: 2222&lt;br/&gt;
	at java.util.ArrayList.RangeCheck(ArrayList.java:547)&lt;br/&gt;
	at java.util.ArrayList.remove(ArrayList.java:387)&lt;br/&gt;
	at org.apache.hadoop.hbase.client.HConnectionManager$HConnectionImplementation.processBatchOfPuts(HConnectionManager.java:1252)&lt;br/&gt;
	at org.apache.hadoop.hbase.client.HTable.flushCommits(HTable.java:826)&lt;br/&gt;
	at org.apache.hadoop.hbase.client.HTable.doPut(HTable.java:682)&lt;br/&gt;
	at org.apache.hadoop.hbase.client.HTable.put(HTable.java:667)&lt;/p&gt;</description>
