                            <comment id="13069962" author="yuzhihong@gmail.com" created="Sat, 23 Jul 2011 14:31:11 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;HTable has always been thread unsafe.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13070065" author="stack" created="Sat, 23 Jul 2011 21:57:31 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Yes, what Ted says.  At head of class it says &quot;This class is not thread safe for updates; the underlying write buffer can be corrupted if multiple threads contend over a single HTable instance.&quot;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Can we close this issue?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
